	<p class="cs709C557D"><span class="cs5E1DB61D">WEST virginia legislature</span></p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">2026 regular session</span></p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">ENGROSSED</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">Committee Substitute</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">for</span></p><p class="cs3E63B65"><span class="cs8498B7A6">House Bill 4215</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="csADC6E5DB">BY Delegate D. Smith</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Originating in the Committee on Health and Human Resources; Reported on January 21, 2026]</span></p><p class="cs29F66C3F"><span class="csEF05ACC">A BILL to amend and reenact &sect;64-5-1 </span><span class="cs93AB6E8B">et seq.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> of the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, to amend and reenact &sect;64-5B-1 et </span><span class="cs93AB6E8B">seq.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> of the Code, and to amend the Code by adding thereto a new article, designated &sect;64-5C-1; relating to authorizing certain agencies of the Department of Health, the Office of Inspector General, and the Department of Health Facilities to promulgate legislative rules; authorizing the rules as filed, as modified, as amended, and as amended and modified by the Legislative Rule-Making Review Committee; authorizing the Department of Health to promulgate a legislative rule relating to water well regulations; authorizing the Department of Health to promulgate a legislative rule relating to lead abatement licensing; authorizing the Department of Health to promulgate a legislative rule relating to emergency medical services; authorizing the Department of Health to promulgate a legislative rule relating to fees for services; authorizing the Department of Health to promulgate a legislative rule relating to clinical laboratory practitioner licensure; authorizing the Department of Health to promulgate a legislative rule relating to distribution of state funds for support of local boards of health; </span><a name="_Hlk219635541"><span class="csEF05ACC">authorizing the Department of Health to promulgate a legislative rule relating to basic public health service standards for local boards of health</span></a><span class="csEF05ACC">; authorizing the Department of Health to promulgate a legislative rule relating to diabetes self-management education; and authorizing the Department of Health to promulgate a legislative rule relating to the exemption from Certificate of Need; authorizing the Office of Inspector General to promulgate a legislative rule relating to nursing home licensure; authorizing the Office of Inspector General to promulgate a legislative rule relating to delegation of medication administration and health maintenance tasks to approved medication assistive personnel; authorizing the Office of Inspector General to promulgate a legislative rule relating to assisted living residences; authorizing the Office of Inspector General to promulgate a legislative rule relating to syringe services program licensure; authorizing the Office of Inspector General to promulgate a legislative rule relating to behavioral health centers licensure; and authorizing the Department of Health Facilities to promulgate a legislative rule relating to patient rights at state-operated mental health facilities.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia: </span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">ARTICLE 5. Authorization for Department of health to promulgate legislative rules.</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csB9803513">&sect;64- 5 - 1. Department of Health. </span></h4>
	<ol start="1" style="margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;">
		<li class="cs579E14CB"><span class="csEF05ACC">The legislative rule filed in the State Register on April 2, 2008, authorized under the authority of &sect;16-1-4 of this code, relating to the Department of Health (water well regulations, <a class="csE6119F9E" href="http://apps.sos.wv.gov/adlaw/csr/rule.aspx?rule=64-19"><span class="cs669A0239">64 CSR 19</span></a></span><span class="csEF05ACC">), is authorized with the amendment set forth below: </span></li></ol>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">By striking out everything after the section 1 heading and inserting in lieu thereof to read as follows: </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	1.1. &nbsp;Scope. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;This legislative rule establishes the certification requirements for water well drillers; pump installers, and the issuance of permits for water wells. The purpose is to protect the public health, protect and prevent contamination in groundwater, and ensure fair and equitable rules for the construction of water wells and installing pumps and pumping equipment in the State of West Virginia.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	1.2. &nbsp;Authority. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;W. Va. &nbsp;Code &sect;&sect;16-1-4, 16-1-6(n), 16-1-9, and 16-1-9a.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	1.3. &nbsp;Filing Date. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class="cs68EFC440">April 2, 2008</span><span class="csEF05ACC">.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	1.4. &nbsp;Effective Date. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;</span><span class="cs68EFC440">April 2, 2008</span><span class="csEF05ACC">.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 162pt left 180pt left 198pt left 216pt left 234pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	1.5. &nbsp;</span><span class="cs68EFC440">Repeal and Replacement of Former Rules. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;This legislative rule repeals and replaces Department of Health rule, Water Well Regulations, 64CSR19, 1989</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">Sunset Provision. -- &nbsp;This rule shall terminate and have no further force or effect on August 1, 2028. &nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csB9803513">&sect;64-19-2. &nbsp;Application and Enforcement.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	2.1. Application. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;This rule applies to all water well drillers and pump installers where the pump is situated in a water well or pulls water from a well.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	2.2. &nbsp;Enforcement. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;This rule shall be enforced by the Commissioner.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csB9803513">64-19-3. &nbsp;Definitions.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.1. Application. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;The Bureau&rsquo;s standard forms for applying for well driller and pump installer certification, water well permit, or permit modification, including any additions, revisions, or modifications to the form.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.2. &nbsp;Apprentice. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;A person working under the direction of a master or journeyman well driller or a pump installer. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.3. &nbsp;Bureau. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;The Bureau for Public Health in the West Virginia Department of Health </span><span class="cs68EFC440">and Human Resources</span><span class="csEF05ACC">.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.4. &nbsp;Casing. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;Pipe or tubing, constructed of specific materials with specified dimensions and weights, that is installed in a borehole during or after completion of the borehole to support the side of the hole and thereby prevent caving, to allow completion of the well, to prevent formation material from entering the well, and to prevent entry of undesirable water into the well.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.5. &nbsp;Certified Well Driller. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;An individual granted a written certificate by the Commissioner to drill, construct, alter, or abandon water wells who meets the requirements of this rule.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.6. &nbsp;Commercial Well -- A well that serves small businesses and facilities in which water is the prime ingredient of the service rendered.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.7. &nbsp;Commissioner. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;The Commissioner of the West Virginia Bureau for Public Health or his or her designee.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.8. &nbsp;Continuing Education Hour. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;One hour of participation in an organized continuing education experience under the direction of a sponsor approved by the Commissioner for renewal of a certification. One Continuing Education Hour is equal to one point.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.9. &nbsp;Design Standards. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;Those specifications, drawings, and other details promulgated by the Commissioner to ensure proper location, design, construction, completion and abandonment of water wells and installation or removal of water pumps as referenced in the Bureau&rsquo;s rules, Water Well Design Standards, 64CSR46, and Public Water System Design Standards, 64CSR77.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.10. &nbsp;Dewatering Well. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;A well used to lower groundwater levels to allow for construction of footings, sewer lines, building foundations, dams, etc. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.11. &nbsp;Hand Dug Well. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;A manually excavated well of a permanent nature installed for water supply. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.12. &nbsp;Heat Pump or Geothermal Well. -- Any well constructed to use the heat exchange properties of either groundwater or of geologic material penetrated by the well.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.13. &nbsp;Inactive Well. -- A well that is no longer actively used. &nbsp;It shall have a sanitary well cap and remain in a state of repair to prevent contamination from entering the well. &nbsp;It may be used in the future or be properly abandoned.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">3.14. &nbsp;Industrial Well. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;A well used in industrial processing, fire protection, washing, packing, or manufacturing of a product excluding food and beverages, or similar non-potable uses.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.15. &nbsp;Irrigation Well. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;A well used to provide water for plants, livestock, or other agricultural processes.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.16. &nbsp;Journeyman Well Driller. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;A person certified by the Commissioner to practice well drilling under the general supervision of a master well driller.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.17. &nbsp;Master Well Driller. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;A person certified by the Commissioner to practice well drilling including pump and pumping equipment installation, and removal, when maintenance or repair of a well is required.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.18. &nbsp;Person. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;An individual, partnership, association, syndicate, company, firm, trust, corporation, government corporation, institution, department, division, bureau, agency, federal agency, or any other entity recognized by law.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.19. &nbsp;Potable Water. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;Water free from impurities in amounts sufficient to cause disease or harmful physiological effects, with bacteriological, chemical, physical, and radiological quality conforming to applicable rules and standards of the Bureau for Public Health.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.20. &nbsp;Potable Water Well. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;Any water well that provides potable water, other than a public water supply for human consumption.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.21. &nbsp;Public Water System. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;Any water supply or system that regularly supplies or offers to supply water for human consumption through pipes or other constructed conveyances, if serving at least an average of </span><span class="cs68EFC440">twenty-five</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">25</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> individuals per day for at least </span><span class="cs68EFC440">sixty</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">60</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> days per year, or which has at least </span><span class="cs68EFC440">fifteen</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">15</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> service connections, and includes:</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">3.21.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">3.21.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Any collection, treatment, storage, and distribution facilities under the control of the owner or operator of the system and used primarily in connection with the system; and </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">3.21.b.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">3.21.2.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Any collection or pretreatment storage facilities not under such control which are used primarily in connection with the system. &nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">3.21.c.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">3.21.3.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;A public water system does not include a system which meets all of the following conditions:</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">3.21.c.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">3.21.3.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;It consists only of distribution and storage facilities and does not have any collection and treatment facilities;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">3.21.c.2.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">3.21.3.b.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;It obtains all of its water from, but is not owned or operated by a public water system that otherwise meets the definition; </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">3.21.c.3.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">3.21.3.c.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;It does not sell water to any person; and </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">3.21.c.4.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">3.21.3.d.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;It is not a carrier conveying passengers in interstate commerce. &nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.22. &nbsp;Pump. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;Any mechanical equipment or device used to transfer water from a well.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.23. &nbsp;Pump Installation Contractor. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;An entity that contracts or agrees to perform a service or function related to any portion of installing a pump or pumping equipment into a water well or public water supply in exchange for money or comparable compensation.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.24. &nbsp;Pump Installer. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;Any person who engages for compensation in pump or pumping equipment installation, removal, alteration, or repair and who is certified by the Commissioner to practice pump and pumping equipment installation to withdraw water from a well.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.25. &nbsp;Pumping Equipment. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;Equipment or related materials that are used or intended to assist withdrawing groundwater from a well, including seals and other safeguards to protect the water from contamination; associated fittings; intake and discharge piping; controls to provide sanitary water storage facilities; and deliver water to a distribution piping system. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.26. &nbsp;Test Wells (Exploratory/ Observation). &nbsp;-- &nbsp;A well that is used to obtain information on groundwater quantity; quality; aquifer characteristics; and availability of production water supply for manufacturing, commercial, and industrial facilities.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.27. &nbsp;Water Return Well. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;A well constructed for returning water that has passed through the heat pump system to the subsurface. &nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.28. &nbsp;Water Well. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;Any excavation or penetration in the ground, whether drilled, bored, cored, driven, washed, jetted, hand dug, or otherwise constructed that enters or passes through an aquifer for purposes that may include, but are not limited to, a potable water supply, exploration for water, industrial, irrigation, commercial, dewatering, or geothermal heat pump wells, and water return wells. &nbsp;This definition shall not include ground water monitoring activities, and all activities for the exploration, development, production, storage, and recovery of coal, oil, and gas and other mineral resources regulated under Chapters 22, 22a, or 22b of the W. Va. Code. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.29. &nbsp;Water Well Contractor. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;Any individual, partnership, syndicate, association, company, firm, trust, corporation, or any other entity that contracts to drill, construct, alter, or abandon water wells in the State of West Virginia.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.30. &nbsp;Well Completion Report. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;A record, accurately kept at the time of drilling, showing the depth; thickness and character of the different strata penetrated; location of water-bearing strata; water level; depth; size, type, and amount of casing installed; location of the well; owner; driller; pump installer; date the well was completed; information on any permanent well pumping equipment installed by the well driller or pump installer; and any other information required by the Commissioner.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">3.30.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">3.30.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;For geothermal and dewatering wells, one completion form, indicating well locations, is required for a system regardless of the number of wells.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">3.30.b.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">3.30.2.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;If wells vary in depth or geology, a single representative geologic log for each type is required. &nbsp;Water bearing zones, any voids, and coal seams or voids, or both penetrated shall be documented on the geologic log indicating appropriate depths. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	3.31. &nbsp;Well Driller. &nbsp;-- &nbsp;An individual who engages in water well drilling, construction, alteration, or abandonment, or who supervises these activities.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csB9803513">&sect;64-19-4. &nbsp;Permits to Install.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	4.1. &nbsp;</span><span class="cs68EFC440">After the effective date of this rule, no</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">No</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> person shall drill, construct, alter, or abandon a water well unless the Commissioner, pursuant to this rule, has issued a valid permit, except where the emergency procedures set forth in subsection 4.3 of this rule apply. &nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	4.2. &nbsp;A permit to drill, construct, alter, or abandon a water well shall be obtained jointly by the water well contractor and property owner. &nbsp;Application for the permit shall be made at least </span><span class="cs68EFC440">fifteen</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">15</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> calendar days prior to the actual well drilling, construction, alteration, or abandonment unless emergency conditions prevail as set forth in subsection 4.3 of this rule.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	4.3. &nbsp;The following applies to emergency water well permits:</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">4.3.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">4.3.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;The Commissioner may issue an emergency water well permit to minimize actual or potential harm to human health, the environment, or property;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">4.3.b.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">4.3.2.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;A certified well driller requesting an emergency permit under this section shall contact the Commissioner no later than the next business day after the emergency occurs. &nbsp;The certified well driller shall submit a completed water well permit application and a well completion report to the Commissioner within five calendar days after the initial contact is made; and</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">4.3.b.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">4.3.2.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;The application shall include a clear and concise factual description of the nature and scope of the emergency.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">4.3.c.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">4.3.3.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;The Commissioner, upon issuance of an emergency permit, shall assign to the well driller an emergency permit number and specify the date of approval. The well driller shall make the approved permit available for any on-site inspection by authorized representatives.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	4.4. &nbsp;Water wells shall be drilled, constructed, altered, or abandoned in accordance with the Bureau&rsquo;s rules, Water Well Design Standards, 64CSR46, and Public Water Systems Design Standards, 64CSR77. &nbsp;These standards constitute the minimum standards for the drilling, construction, alteration, or abandonment of a water well, pump, and pumping equipment. &nbsp;Any plans approved by the Commissioner pursuant to this rule shall be in substantial compliance with this rule-mentioned standards. &nbsp;Where applicable, an underground injection control permit shall be obtained from the West Virginia Department of Environmental Protection </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">(DEP)</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> in compliance with DEP&rsquo;s rule, Underground Injection Control, 47CSR13, prior to construction for a water well. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	4.5. &nbsp;Application for a permit to construct, alter, and abandon water wells shall be made to the Commissioner on forms prescribed by the Commissioner. The master water well driller and property owner shall jointly sign this application. &nbsp;By signing the application, the property owner acknowledges that the information provided on the application is true; the property owner is responsible for informing the certified well driller of the location of any known existing or proposed on-site sewage systems and ensuring that these systems are in compliance with all applicable state rules.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D" style="tab-stops:left 18pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	4.6. &nbsp;In cases where a water well contractor is changed, the applicable permits shall be reissued to reflect these changes prior to construction. &nbsp;No additional permit fee is required.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D" style="tab-stops:left 18pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	4.7. &nbsp;In the event the permit application is denied, the Commissioner shall state, in writing, the one or more reasons for denial and furnish it to the applicant within </span><span class="cs68EFC440">fifteen</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">15</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> calendar days from receipt of the permit application.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	4.8. &nbsp;A permit, unless revoked, is valid for a period of one year from the date of issuance. In the event the construction or alteration is not completed within that time, the Commissioner may extend the time limit upon written request by the permittee. &nbsp;If the water well is not constructed within the appropriate period, a new well permit shall be obtained from the Commissioner prior to the start of any well drilling activity pursuant to subsection 4.5 of this rule. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	4.9. &nbsp;The Commissioner may revoke or deny a permit to install if the applicant or permittee fails to comply with the provisions of the permit, any applicable provision of the rules, or orders issued pursuant thereto. &nbsp;The revocation or denial shall be in writing and shall state the reasons for revocation or denial.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	4.10. &nbsp;Any person</span><span class="cs68EFC440">,</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> whose application for a permit to construct a water well system </span><span class="cs68EFC440">that</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> has been revoked or denied, may, within </span><span class="cs68EFC440">thirty</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">30</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> calendar days from receipt of the permit denial or revocation, request a hearing in accordance with section 14 of this rule.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	4.11. &nbsp;The following activities may be conducted by a certified well driller without an individual permit issued by the Commissioner:</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">4.11.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">4.11.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;The repair of any well, including redevelopment, cleaning, or screen replacements, provided that this does not include deepening of the well; and</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">4.11.b.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">4.11.2.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Acidizing a well.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	4.12. &nbsp;The Commissioner may inspect the well site, well logging, grouting, and provide for taking of geologic or water samples, or both.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	4.13. &nbsp;The Commissioner may charge a fee for each permitting service listed in Appendix A of this rule.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	4.14. &nbsp;Upon issuance of a permit, the Commissioner shall provide the owner and contractor with information prepared by the Commissioner explaining the importance of water well sampling, the procedures for sampling, and how the water can be tested to assure a safe supply of water.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csB9803513">&sect;64-19-5. &nbsp;Records of Completed Water Wells. </span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	5.1. &nbsp;Within </span><span class="cs68EFC440">thirty (</span><span class="csEF05ACC">30</span><span class="cs68EFC440">)</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> calendar days after the water well has been constructed, altered, or abandoned, the certified well driller shall submit a completion report to the Commissioner. &nbsp;The date of construction and time of completion is the date and time the rig is removed or pulled off the borehole or well. &nbsp;The certified well driller who actually performed the construction, alteration, or abandonment of the well or provided the on-site supervision of the well construction, alteration, or abandonment shall sign the completion report. &nbsp;A master well driller is required to sign the completion report when a journeyman well driller conducts the on-site supervision and drilling. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	5.2. &nbsp;Completion reports shall be filed for pump installation. When the pumping equipment is installed after the record of completion has been submitted, the record shall be amended by the certified well driller or pump installer and resubmitted to the Commissioner within </span><span class="cs68EFC440">thirty</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">30</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> calendar days of installation of the pumping equipment. The certified well driller or pump installer who actually performed the installation of the pump system shall sign the amended record of completion. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		5.2.a. &nbsp;A completion report is not required for the repair of pumps or the replacement of pumps or pumping equipment if the depth of the setting and efficiency are not affected. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	5.3. &nbsp;The contractor shall provide two copies of the completion report to the Commissioner and one &nbsp;copy of the completion report to the owner.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csB9803513">&sect;64-19-6. &nbsp;General Provisions for well driller certifications of the proper class and pump installer certifications.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	6.1. &nbsp;No person shall drill, construct, alter, or abandon any water well without possessing a valid West Virginia certification of the proper class issued by the Commissioner and complying with the applicable sections of this rule.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	6.2. &nbsp;No person shall install, repair, or replace a well pump or well pumping equipment or engage in that business without possessing a valid West Virginia certification of the proper class issued by the Commissioner and complying with applicable sections of this rule. A property owner may be allowed to install the pump system and sign the completion record if, prior to the installation</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">,</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> the property owner passes an examination administered by the Commissioner with a minimum score of </span><span class="cs68EFC440">seventy</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">70</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> percent. &nbsp;This examination shall demonstrate the individual&rsquo;s knowledge of the applicable rules.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	6.3. &nbsp;Well drillers shall be classified into one of three classes: master well driller; journeyman well driller; or an apprentice well driller.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.3.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.3.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;A certified master well driller, after meeting the requirements of subsection 9.2 of this rule</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">,</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> may:</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.3.a.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.3.1.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Drill, construct, install, repair, replace, alter, or abandon water wells, including public water supply wells; </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.3.a.2.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.3.1.b.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Install or replace well pumping equipment and appurtenances, storage tanks &nbsp;&nbsp;and connecting lines between a well and storage tank;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.3.a.3.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.3.1.c.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Perform yield and drawdown testing of wells</span><span class="cs68EFC440">;</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> and supervise journeymen well drillers and apprentices;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.3.a.4.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.3.1.d.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Sign permit applications and certify that a well has been drilled, constructed, installed, repaired, modified, altered, or abandoned in conformance with all applicable state and well drill and pump installation standards; </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.3.a.5.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.3.1.e.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Qualify as a candidate to be appointed to the Advisory Board; </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.3.a.6.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.3.1.f.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Supervise journeymen and apprentices; and</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.3.a.7.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.3.1.g.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Perform field observations to verify qualifications of applicants for all certifications covered by this rule. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.3.b.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.3.2.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;A certified journeymen well driller, after meeting all of the requirements of subsection 9.2 of this rule, may:</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.3.b.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.3.2.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Drill, construct, install, repair, replace, alter, or abandon a well, except a public water system&rsquo;s supply wells;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.3.b.2.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.3.2.b.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Install or replace well pumping equipment and appurtenances, storage tanks, and connecting lines between a well and storage tank; </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.3.b.3.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.3.2.c.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Perform yield and drawdown testing of wells; and </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.3.b.4.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.3.2.d.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Supervise apprentices. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.3.c.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.3.3.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;An apprentice may perform well drilling as a well driller only under the immediate on-site supervision of a master or journeyman well driller. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.3.d.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.3.4.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;A journeyman or master well driller shall be on-site in direct charge of drilling, constructing, altering, or abandoning a water well.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	6.4. &nbsp;Pump installers shall be classified into two classes, as a certified pump installer or an apprentice. &nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.4.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.4.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;A certified pump installer, after meeting the requirements of subsection 9.2 of this rule, may:</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.4.a.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.4.1.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Install or replace well pumping equipment and appurtenances, pressure tanks, and connecting lines between a well and storage tank;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.4.a.2.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.4.1.b.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Qualify as a candidate for appointment to the Advisory Board; and </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.4.a.3.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.4.1.c.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Perform yield and drawdown testing of wells.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">6.4.b.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">6.4.2.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;An apprentice may perform pump installations, and replace appurtenances, pressure tanks, and connecting lines while under the immediate on-site supervision of a master or journeyman well driller</span><span class="cs68EFC440">,</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> or pump installer. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	6.5. &nbsp;A certified </span><span class="cs68EFC440">person</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">pump installer or water well driller</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> shall have in her or his possession a valid certification for the proper class at all times during any operations. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	6.6. &nbsp;A certified pump installer or water well driller may run power and control wiring from the disconnect box and breaker panel to water well equipment without obtaining an electrician&rsquo;s license. A certification issued pursuant to this rule does not authorize the certificate holder to alter the existing electrical service to any building or structure or perform any other electrical work covered by any national, state, or local codes and ordinances, if the latter are more restrictive.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	6.7. &nbsp;A certified or licensed plumber may provide plumbing services as a plumbing contractor to install pressure switches, pressure tanks, valves, and pipes without holding certifications from the Commissioner. The certified or licensed plumber shall not break the well seal or alter, cut, or drill into the casing </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">for the purpose of performing repairs to the pumping equipment or appurtenances</span><span class="csEF05ACC">, unless he or she is certified as a pump installer </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">or passes an examination administered by the Commissioner with a minimum score of 70 percent and completes two hours of continuing education related to pump installation each year as evidenced by submission of a certificate of continuing education completion. This subsection shall not apply to wells utilized by public water systems.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	6.8. &nbsp;A certified or licensed electrician may </span><span class="cs68EFC440">do</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">perform</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> electrical contracting, repair, or install pressure switches, control boxes, and other electrical components of the pumping equipment without holding certifications issued by the Commissioner. The electrician shall adhere to these rules for the installation and may not break the well seal or alter, cut, or drill into the casing, unless the certified or licensed electrician is certified as a pump installer.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csB9803513">&sect;64-19-7. &nbsp;Application and Certification Examination Procedures and Fee Requirements. &nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	7.1. &nbsp;An applicant for a West Virginia master well drilling certification shall:</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">7.1.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">7.1.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Submit an application on the forms prescribed by the Commissioner</span><span class="cs68EFC440"> pursuant to satisfying all experience and other requirements specified</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> and provide evidence of the following:</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54p