left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	</span><span class="cs68EFC440">7.10.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">7.9.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;</span><span class="cs68EFC440">For an</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">An</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> individual who holds a legal certification or who has practiced well drilling in accordance with all laws and rules in a state that does not have comparable certification classes, the applicant shall have acquired the following experience:</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">7.10.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">7.9.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;For a master well driller - Six years of well drilling experience; </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">7.10.b.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">7.9.2.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;For a journeyman driller - Four years of well drilling experience; or</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">7.10.c.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">7.9.3.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;For a pump installer - Three years of pump installation experience; and</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">7.10.d.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">7.9.4.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;For all classes each individual shall have passed </span><span class="cs68EFC440">any</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">all</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> written examination requirements and obtained a minimum grade of </span><span class="cs68EFC440">seventy</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">70</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> percent on each portion of the </span><span class="cs68EFC440">one or more</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> written examination and any other requirements determined necessary by the Commissioner. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	</span><span class="cs68EFC440">7.11.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">7.10.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;The Commissioner may review applications from individuals who hold a legal certification for well drilling in another state with comparable certification classes. The Commissioner may grant a comparable certification for the applicant if appropriate. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	</span><span class="cs68EFC440">7.12.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">7.11.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;All certifications expire </span><span class="cs68EFC440">one year</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">two years</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> from the date of issuance and shall be renewed </span><span class="cs68EFC440">thirty</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">30</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> days prior to expiration. The applicant shall submit a completed renewal on forms provided by the Commissioner. &nbsp;Applicants shall provide evidence of bonding and insurance as required by section 8 of this rule. Applicants shall supply evidence of continuing education requirements in accordance with section 9 of this rule for certification renewal.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csB9803513">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">7.12.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">7.11.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;A certificate holder who fails to renew his or her certification within six months following the </span><span class="cs68EFC440">renewal</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">expiration</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> date of the certification shall not have the certification reinstated until he or she successfully passes the written examinations or field test prescribed by the Commissioner for applicants for a new certificate. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	</span><span class="cs68EFC440">7.14.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">7.12.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;A certificate holder may place his or her certification on inactive status for a two-year period if the certificate holder has submitted an application for inactive status </span><span class="cs68EFC440">within sixty</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">at least 60</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> days before the expiration date of the certificate. Before the Commissioner reactivates the certificate of an inactive-status certificate, that certificate holder shall satisfy any renewal requirements.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	</span><span class="cs68EFC440">7.15.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">7.13.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;A certificate holder may obtain a duplicate certificate to replace a certificate that has been lost, destroyed, or mutilated if the certificate holder makes a written</span><span class="cs68EFC440">, notarized</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> request to the Commissioner, stating the reason for the request. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	</span><span class="cs68EFC440">7.16.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">7.14.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;The Commissioner may charge a fee for each certification service provided as listed in Appendix B of this rule.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csB9803513">&sect;64-19-8. &nbsp;Bonding of Water Well and Pump Installation Contractors. &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csB9803513">	</span><span class="csEF05ACC">8.1. &nbsp;Each water well and pump installation contractor shall have a current contractor&rsquo;s bond payable to the Commissioner upon forfeiture and liability insurance coverage effective throughout West Virginia in a form determined by the Commissioner. &nbsp;The Commissioner shall determine the amount of the contractor&rsquo;s bond, which may not exceed </span><span class="cs68EFC440">five thousand dollars</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">$5,000</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &nbsp;Lack of a current contractor&rsquo;s bond is considered sufficient grounds for denial of a water well or pump installation permit. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	8.2. &nbsp;Forfeiture of the contractor&rsquo;s bond is predicated upon a failure to drill, construct, repair, replace, alter, or abandon a well or upon installation of a pump in a water well in accordance with this rule and the Bureau&rsquo;s rule, Water Well Design Standards, 64CSR46. &nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	8.3. &nbsp;The surety shall have the option of forfeiting the contractor&rsquo;s bond or completing the well in accordance with this rule and standards specified in subsection 8.2 of this rule. &nbsp;The Commissioner shall expend all proceeds from a forfeiture </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">due to failure</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> to alter or abandon the well in accordance with applicable rules and standards. &nbsp;The Commissioner shall retain and expend any excess funds </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">collected</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> for the purpose of altering or abandoning water wells in accordance with applicable rules and standards. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	8.4. &nbsp;The surety shall have the option of canceling a contractor&rsquo;s bond after providing notice to the Commissioner at least </span><span class="cs68EFC440">thirty</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">30</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> days prior to cancellation. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	8.5. &nbsp;In lieu of the bond required by subsection 8.1 of this rule, the Commissioner may accept an irrevocable letter of credit issued by a bank chartered by the State of West Virginia or a member bank of the federal reserve system. &nbsp;Confirmation of the irrevocable letter of credit shall be in writing and shall be signed by the issuing or confirming bank.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csB9803513">&sect;64-19-9. &nbsp;Continuing Education Program and Requirements.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	9.1. &nbsp;The continuing education program shall be a formal offering of instruction or information to certificate holders and registrants for the purpose of maintaining, enhancing, and developing the skills necessary for the protection of groundwater and the health and general welfare of the citizens and to increase the competence of well drillers and pump installers.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	9.2. &nbsp;</span><span class="cs68EFC440">Beginning two years after the effective date of this rule, a</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">A</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> certified master well driller shall show proof of </span><span class="cs68EFC440">three hours</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">six hours</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> of continuing education related to water well drilling every </span><span class="cs68EFC440">year</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">two years</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &nbsp;Additionally, for a certified master well driller to install pumps, he or she shall show proof of </span><span class="cs68EFC440">two</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">four </span><span class="csEF05ACC">hours of continuing education related to pump installation every </span><span class="cs68EFC440">year</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">two years</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &nbsp;A certified journeyman driller shall show proof of </span><span class="cs68EFC440">two</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">four</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> hours of continuing education every </span><span class="cs68EFC440">year</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">two years</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. For a certified journeyman driller to install pumps, the journeyman driller shall show proof of </span><span class="cs68EFC440">one hour</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">two hours</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> of continuing education related to pump installation every </span><span class="cs68EFC440">year</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">two years</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &nbsp;</span><span class="cs68EFC440">The</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">A</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> certified pump installer shall show proof of </span><span class="cs68EFC440">two</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">four</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> hours of continuing education every </span><span class="cs68EFC440">year</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">two years</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> to maintain the certification. &nbsp;Each certificate holder shall submit a copy of the certificates of completion as proof of meeting the continuing education requirements. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	9.3. &nbsp;Only courses or programs designated or approved by the Commissioner are acceptable for continuing education.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	9.4. &nbsp;To obtain pre-approval of a course the sponsor or attendee shall submit the following information to the Commissioner: &nbsp;a written course description, which includes the names and qualifications of the presenters; the time and location of the course; the proposed number of hours; and the program objectives. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	9.5. &nbsp;Programs for continuing education units may be held in state or out of state. Approved topics include water wells or pump system technology, science, health, sound business practices, rule compliance, </span><span class="cs68EFC440">including other governmental</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> and industry requirements, including worker health and safety.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	9.6. &nbsp;Program sponsors shall provide proof of attendance to attendees. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csB9803513">&sect;64-19-10. &nbsp;Identification Numbers of Water Well Rigs and Well Head. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	10.1. &nbsp;All </span><span class="cs68EFC440">water well contractors shall ensure that all</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> water well rigs </span><span class="cs68EFC440">they use or those used by their employees are</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">shall be</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> clearly marked with legible and plainly visible identification numbers at all times.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	10.2. &nbsp;The identification number to be used on water well drilling rigs is the certification number of the water well driller at the well site who is responsible for the water well drilling operations.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	10.3. &nbsp;Certification numbers shall be printed on each side of every water well drilling rig in numerals </span><span class="cs68EFC440">of</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> not less than two inches high </span><span class="cs68EFC440">and the numerals shall be</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> in a color sufficiently different from the color of the vehicle or equipment so that the certification number is plainly legible.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	</span><span class="cs68EFC440">10.4. &nbsp;Water well contractors shall ensure that all water well rigs they use or those used by their employees are clearly marked as provided in subsections 10.2 and 10.3 of this rule.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	</span><span class="cs68EFC440">10.5.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">10.4.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Each well drilling contractor shall securely attach a metal tag or engraved well cap to the wellhead containing the following information: the contractor&#39;s name, address, and permit number; the depth of the well; and the date of construction or alteration.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csB9803513">&sect;64-19-11. &nbsp;Advisory Board. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	11.1. &nbsp;The Commissioner may establish an advisory board and designate the chairman of the board.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	11.2. &nbsp;The advisory board membership shall consist of, but not necessarily be limited to, the following members:</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">11.2.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">11.2.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Three certified master well drillers; </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">11.2.a.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">11.2.1.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;These three members </span><span class="cs68EFC440">may</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">shall</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> represent and have actual experience from the various geologic areas of the state and be familiar with the various appropriate drilling methods used in different regions of West Virginia.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">11.2.b.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">11.2.2.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;One certified pump installer;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">11.2.c.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">11.2.3.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;One employee of the West Virginia Bureau for Public Health;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">11.2.d.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">11.2.4.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;One representative from a local health department;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">11.2.e.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">11.2.5.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;One employee of the West Virginia Department of Environmental Protection;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">11.2.f.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">11.2.6.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;One individual who is not employed by the state and who has no commercial or economic involvement in well drilling or pump installation;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">11.2.g.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">11.2.7.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;One academic or technical expert who is either:</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">11.2.g.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">11.2.7.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Employed by the West Virginia Geological Survey or the United States Geological Survey;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">11.2.g.2.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">11.2.7.b.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;A professional hydrologist or hydrogeologist; or</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span><span class="cs68EFC440">11.2.g.3.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">11.2.7.c.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;A geology or hydrogeology professor from a college or university in West Virginia.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	11.3. &nbsp;The Water Well Advisory Board </span><span class="cs68EFC440">may exercise</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">has</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> the following duties:</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">11.3.a.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">11.3.1.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Recommend changes in the certification program as needed to the Commissioner;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">11.3.b. &nbsp;Receive complaints regarding certification issues and appeals of certification decisions and recommend follow up actions to the Commissioner;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">11.3.c.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">11.3.2.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Recommend written tests and field tests required for certification and assist in the preparation and administration of written tests, as appropriate;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">11.3.d.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">11.3.3.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Recommend continuing education classes and instructors; and</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">		</span><span class="cs68EFC440">11.3.e.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">11.3.4.</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> &nbsp;Perform other duties that may be assigned by the Commissioner.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csB9803513">&sect;64-19-12. &nbsp;Inspections and Water Sampling.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">12.1. &nbsp;</span><span class="csEF05ACC">The Commissioner may make as many inspections as necessary, during the construction, installation, modification, or operation of a water well, pump, and pumping equipment to determine compliance with the applicable provisions of this rule and the Bureau&rsquo;s rule, Water Well Design Standards, 64CSR46. &nbsp;An inspection may include, without limitation, water sampling for the detection of any contaminants, the documentation of a violation of construction standards, technical procedures, or any other requirements established under the rule. &nbsp;The owner or occupant of a dwelling, establishment, or land where a water well is located shall provide the Commissioner access for making the inspection. &nbsp;The Commissioner shall record the findings of inspections on forms prescribed for </span><span class="cs68EFC440">the</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">that</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> purpose. </span><a name="_Toc162141314"></a></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csB9803513">&sect;64-19-13. &nbsp;Penalties, Suspension, and Revocation of Certifications.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csB9803513">	</span><span class="csEF05ACC">13.1. &nbsp;Persons who violate the provisions of this rule are subject to the civil and administrative penalties of W. Va. Code &sect;6-1-9a and to potential civil or criminal penalties under W. Va. Code &sect;16-1-9, </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">&sect;</span><span class="csEF05ACC">16-1-9a, and </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">&sect;</span><span class="csEF05ACC">16-1-18.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	13.2. &nbsp;The Commissioner may suspend, revoke, or deny certification of a driller or pump installer if the information on the application form is incomplete, inaccurate, false, misleading, or indicates that the provisions of this rule cannot be met. &nbsp;The Commissioner may revoke or suspend the certification of a driller or pump installer who knowingly violates this rule. &nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt left 468pt left 504pt left 540pt left 576pt left 612pt left 648pt left 684pt left 720pt left 756pt left 792pt left 828pt left 864pt left 900pt left 936pt;"><span class="csEF05ACC">	13.3. &nbsp;When certification has been denied, suspended, or revoked, the person affected shall immediately discontinue the drilling, altering, constructing, and abandonment of water wells. </span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B" style="tab-stops:left -54.95pt left -36pt left 0pt left 18pt left 36pt left 54pt left 72pt left 90pt left 108pt left 126pt left 144pt left 180pt left 216pt left 252pt left 288pt left 324pt left 360pt left 396pt left 432pt 